1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the zero-rate error exponent of a channel, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses the Gaussian channel with intersymbol interference, which is a common model in communication systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with a channel whose state variable depends on past inputs, which is a system-theoretic concept. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia applications that involve transmission of data over channels with memory. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper may be relevant to the design and analysis of networking protocols that operate over channels with memory.
